标  题: BE:Oracle HRMS Consultant / Senior Consultant (北京市) 
发信站: 水木社区 (Thu Jul  7 18:17:24 2005), 站内
Job Title 
Consultant (Oracle HR) 
Job Description: 
Be knowledgeable, at a detail level, in the overall functionality of Oracle HRMS components. Understand the business issues and processes of the client organization within the Oracle Human Resources and Payroll areas. Be able to work closely with other team members during project stage. 
Job Responsibilities: 
o Gain a mastery of Oracle HRMS functionalities. Transfer knowledge to other team members as required. 
o Establish a good working relationship with other HR/Payroll team members. 
o Make decisions (and escalate when necessary) relating to HR/Payroll that may affect the organization. 
o Gather and define the detailed functional requirements for HR/Payroll. 
o Analyze and configure the HR/Payroll components in Oracle. 
o Develop detailed scripts that will be used for testing the configuration. 
o Execute test scripts and clearly document the test results. 
o Develop reference documentation including user manuals, help guidelines, and other reference materials. 
o Assist in developing instructional courseware and conducting end user training. 
Job Requirements: 
o Demonstrate an understanding of enterprise-wide HR/Payroll vision. 
o Have in-depth knowledge of China’s standard HR/Payroll business processes. 
o Have knowledge of Oracle Human Resource System and detailed functionality. 
o Have previous Oracle HR/Payroll implementation experience. Implementation experience based on China legislation is preferred but not required. 
o Must be an effective communicator and able to work well within a team environment. 
o Must reasonable English communication skills in speaking, reading and writing. 
mailto:weibin.chen@bearingpoint.com

